I need to sync the animations of my tiled map tiles with other objects in the game. Thus I need to know which animated frame is currently drawn per tile.

There is already a (private) method `getCurrentFrame()`, which could be used for that. I think all that is necessary is to add a new property to the class, something like `int currentFrameIndex`, which would be set to `i` in the first line of the `for` loop, like this:

```
private TiledMapTile getCurrentFrame() {
    int currentTime = (int)(lastTiledMapRenderTime % loopDuration);
    for (int i = 0; i < animationIntervals.length; ++i){
        currentFrameIndex = i;  // <-- added new line here
        int animationInterval = animationIntervals[i];
        if (currentTime<=animationInterval) return frameTiles[i];
        currentTime -= animationInterval;
    }
    throw new GdxRuntimeException("Could not determine current animation frame in AnimatedTiledMapTile. This should never happen.");
}
```

Now the new method `public int getCurrentFrameIndex()` could simply return `currentFrameIndex`.

Thanks!

